<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-01-31T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-01-31T15:00:00-05:00" n="437" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d437">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">611.2531/255: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Frost</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-01-31T16:00:00-04:00">January 31, 1938—4
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 4:34 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>18. Department’s telegram No. 10, January 22, 3 p.m. Foreign Office will
                            accept note as drafted with additional sentence as follows: “It is
                            understood, however, that if the ratification does not take place
                            with[in] the period authorized by law 5142 the <hi rend="italic">modus
                                vivendi</hi> could be signed again so as to continue in provisional
                            effect.” Purpose is merely to harmonize formula of the note with actual
                            legal possibilities. Please instruct.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Frost</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>